 }}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship=''Olive''\n|flag={{flagcountry|UKGBI|civil}}\n|desc=The [[snow (ship)|snow]] foundered off [[Great Yarmouth]], [[Norfolk]]. Her eight crew were rescued by the fishing boat ''Renaissance'' ({{flag|France}}). ''Olive'' was on a voyage from [[Newcastle upon Tyne]], [[Northumberland]] to London.<ref name=Times281062a/><ref name=HP311062/><ref name=Searlep121>{{cite web |url=http://www.searlecanada.org/sunderland/sunderland121.html |title=SHIPS BUILT AT SUNDERLAND IN THE 1830s |publisher=Searle |accessdate=18 March 2020}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship=''Pandora''\n|flag={{flagcountry|UKGBI|civil}}\n|desc=The [[brig]] foundered off [[Calais]], France. Her crew survived. She was on a voyage from [[Middlesbrough]], [[North Riding of Yorkshire|Yorkshire]] to [[Boulogne-sur-Mer|Boulogne]], [[Pas-de-Calais]], France.<ref name=S251062/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship=''Place''\n|flag={{flagcountry|UKGBI|civil}}\n|desc=The ship was driven ashore at Queen Anne's Battery, [[Plymouth]], [[Devon]] and sank. She was refloated and taken in to [[Sutton Pool]].<ref name=Times241062/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship=''Queen''\n|flag={{flagcountry|UKGBI|civil}}\n|desc=The ship foundered in the North Sea {{convert|25|nmi|km}} off the Dutch coast. She was on a voyage from [[Sunderland, County Durham]] to [[Portsmouth]], [[Hampshire]].<ref name=Times271062/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship=''Robert and Margaret''\n|flag={{flagcountry|UKGBI|civil}}\n|desc=The [[collier (ship type)|collier]], a [[brig]], foundered off the mouth of the [[River Humber]] with the loss of six of her nine crew. Survivors were rescued by the [[smack (ship)|smack]] ''Tartar'' ({{flagcountry|UKGBI|civil}}).<ref name=Times231062a/><ref name=Times281062/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{HMS|Vigilant|1856|6}} \n|flag={{navy|UK}}\n|desc=The {{sclass-|Vigilant|gunvessel}} ran aground on the Gunfleet Sand. She was on a voyage from Scotland to [[Sheerness]], [[