mber 1862 |issue=11939 |page=7 }}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship=''Martha Sawyer'' \n|flag={{flagcountry|UKGBI|civil}}\n|desc=The ship was driven ashore at [[Manicouagan Regional County Municipality|Manicouagan]], [[Province of Canada]], [[British North America]]. She was on a voyage from [[Quebec City]], Province of Canada to [[Conwy]], [[Caernarfonshire]].<ref name=LM261162>{{Cite news |title=Shipping Intelligence |newspaper=Liverpool Mercury |location=Liverpool |date=26 November 1862 |issue=4616 }}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Port Mulgrove|1860|2}} \n|flag={{flagcountry|UKGBI|civil}}\n|desc=The [[steamship]] was wrecked at [[Souter Point]], [[Northumberland]]. Her crew were rescued.<ref name=NC071162/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship=''Ruby'' \n|flag={{flagicon|UKGBI|civil}} [[British North America]]\n|desc=The derelict [[seal hunting|sealer]] was driven ashore on [[Tiree]], [[Inner Hebrides]].<ref name=S171162/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list end}}\n\n==29 October==\n{{shipwreck list begin |date=29 October 1862 |sort=}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship=''Helene'' \n|flag=[[File:Flag of Stralsund.svg|22px]] [[Stralsund]] \n|desc=The [[brig]] capsized in Loch Foltark, [[Skye]], [[Outer Hebrides]], [[United Kingdom of Great Britain and Ireland|United Kingdom]].<ref name=S011162/><ref name=S281162>{{Cite news |title=Mercantile Ship News |newspaper=The Standard |location=London |date=28 November 1862 |issue=11949 |page=7 }}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship=''Phantom''\n|flag={{flagcountry|UKGBI|civil}}\n|desc=The ship sank in the [[North Sea]]. Her crew were rescued by a Danish [[schooner]].<ref name=Times181162>{{Cite newspaper The Times |articlename=Ship News |date=18 November 1862 |page_number=8 |issue=24406 |column=E }}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list end}}\n\n==30 October==\n{{shipwreck list begin |date=30 October 1862 |sort=}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship=''Dove''\n|flag={{flagcountry|UKGBI|civil}}\n|desc=The ship departed from departed from